  "chapter": {
    "number": 51,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Create in Me a Clean Heart, O God"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "hebrew_subtitle",
        "content": [
          "For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David. When Nathan the prophet came to him after his adultery with Bathsheba."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Have mercy on me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4389
          },
          {
            "text": "O God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "according to Your loving devotion;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "according to Your great compassion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "blot out my transgressions.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wash me clean of my iniquity",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and cleanse me from my sin.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I know my transgressions,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my sin is always before me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Against You, You only, have I sinned",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and done what is evil in Your sight,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that You may be proved right when You speak",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and blameless when You judge.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4390
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely I was brought forth in iniquity;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I was sinful when my mother conceived me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely You desire truth in the inmost being;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You teach me wisdom in the inmost place.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Purify me with hyssop, and I will be clean;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let me hear joy and gladness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let the bones You have crushed rejoice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hide Your face from my sins",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and blot out all my iniquities.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Create in me a clean heart, O God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and renew a right spirit within me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cast me not away from Your presence;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "take not Your Holy Spirit from me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Restore to me the joy of Your salvation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sustain me with a willing spirit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then I will teach transgressors Your ways,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sinners will return to You.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Deliver me from bloodguilt, O God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the God of my salvation,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and my tongue will sing of Your righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O Lord, open my lips,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my mouth will declare Your praise.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For You do not delight in sacrifice, or I would bring it;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You take no pleasure in burnt offerings.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a broken and a contrite heart,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "O God, You will not despise.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In Your good pleasure, cause Zion to prosper;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "build up the walls of Jerusalem.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then You will delight in righteous sacrifices,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in whole burnt offerings;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "then bulls will be offered on Your altar.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 4389,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or Be gracious to me",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 51,
          "verse": 1
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 4390,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "LXX and victorious when You judge; cited in Romans 3:4",
        "reference": {
